RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 96. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Start Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LEGISLATOR tracked in the two path in range from mid-pack, went between rivals on the backstretch and far turn, roused at the quarter pole and tipped out to take aim at the leaders from outside, reached the front at the eighth pole, kicked clear midstretch and held safely under a drive. GHOST COAST sat off the pace two wide, angled out into the stretch, finished well but had to settle for second best. CARIBBEAN KING stalked the pace from inside, coaxed along into the lane, put in a rail bid in upper stretch, was no match for the top pair but kept on for the show honors. CAPTAIN CHOOCHIES reserved in the early going and moved inside, ridden along through the far turn, lacked room in traffic in upper stretch, altered out into the clear and kept on for a minor award. PRECISION STRIKE trailed early along the rail, worked on around the far turn and tipped to the two path, angled out in the stretch and summoned a mild rally to improve position. KHANTARO D'ORO stalked in the two path early, moved up to press the pace from between rivals on the backstretch, stayed alongside the leader through the far turn and into the lane, fought to the eighth pole and weakened. SURF AFFAIR vied for the lead inside a pair of rivals on the clubhouse turn, dueled into the backstretch, inched ahead to take control, maintained a short lead through the far turn, lost command at the eighth pole and weakened. MY PARTNER GLEN traveled three deep out of range, rounded the far turn four then three wide and failed to menace. UNCLE REG vied for the lead outside a pair of rivals and four wide into the first turn, pulled and became a bit rank around the bend, stalked four deep in the middle stages, spun five wide into the lane and had little left in the final furlong. BERT'S PROSPECT vied three wide through the clubhouse turn, pressed three deep on the backstretch, lost touch with the leader and chased three then four wide on the far turn, then faded in the drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEDDY'S TRIUMPH sprinted clear early, set all the pace on the inside to the stretch, put to right then left handed urging in upper stretch, got a bit weary on the wrong late but managed to hold. THIRSTY LOV hustled from the gate, switch off the rail to give chase, ran two wide around the bend, continued within range into the final furlong, put in a mild late bid and was gaining to the wire. GRAZEN BOY brushed with inner rival at the start, stalked from inside into the turn, fought the rider on the turn before eventually drifting out with a quarter mile remaining, churned on through the lane and held the show. WINNING BIG chased two wide into the turn, climbed early on the bend and lost ground while moving out to the four path, straightened out in the lane and kept on through the late stages but could not pass GRAZEN BOY for third. PLEASEUSETHEPORTAL brushed with outer rival at the start, raced greenly early and steered out into the clear, traveled four then five wide around the turn and lacked a needed response. SIR LOOKING GLASS chased three wide into the turn, got floated out out to the five path late on the bend and weakened. SEASEID RIDE raced greenly early and dropped back, saved ground lagging far back and was never a factor.

Claiming Price $50,000 (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts Preferred)(Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAZED set the pace under pressure early, dueled inside GYPSY KING through the turn, inched ahead in upper stretch and held gamely under right handed urging. LEMON SUSHI was off slow to begin, pulled hard chasing early, bobbled and took hold briefly at the three-eighths pole, tipped three wide with a quarter mile remaining, rallied from outside and got up for second. GYPSY KING broke well then pressed the pace from outside, dueled around the bend and into the lane, shifted in to bother rival midstretch and finished gamely to the wire but got edged for second. X J RASCAL (IRE) bobbled and got bumped from outside at the start, trailed under a hold early, went three wide into the turn, moved out to the four path then angled in leaving the bend to enter the stretch two wide, steered out in the lane and lacked a rally. MISTER ICEMAN bobbled and bumped inner rival in the beginning, showed keen early foot while tugging the rider along on the inside, saved ground through the turn and never found room in the stretch. HAWKER sat off the pace on the inside, went two wide into the turn, drew closer around the bend, had to pause in traffic in upper stretch, found room and roused at the eighth pole, lost his path and was forced to check midstretch and failed to find room late. KING APOLLO chased four deep early, three deep into the turn, spun five wide into the lane and failed to threaten. ADARE broke a step slow, chased three deep into the turn, moved into the two path the asked three wide into the stretch and failed to make an impact. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY, THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED GYPSY KING FROM THIRD TO SIXTH FOR SHIFTING IN AND CAUSING HAWKER TO STEADY SHARPLY IN MIDSTRETCH, COSTING HIM A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING.

BREATH AWAY (GB) rated along the inside then got put in a bit tight early on the clubhouse turn, ridden along saving ground into the lane, urged left handed in upper stretch and held the show.
